107 /*
108  * The "todecref" argument holds a pointer to PyObject * that must be
109  * DECREF'ed after returned char_u * is no longer needed or NULL if all what
110  * was needed to generate returned value is object.
111  *
112  * Use Py_XDECREF to decrement reference count.
113  */
114  static char_u *
115 StringToChars(PyObject *obj, PyObject **todecref)
116 {
117  char_u *str;
118 
119  if (PyBytes_Check(obj))
120  {
121 
122  if (PyBytes_AsStringAndSize(obj, (char **) &str, NULL) == -1
123  || str == NULL)
124  return NULL;
125 
126  *todecref = NULL;
127  }
128  else if (PyUnicode_Check(obj))
129  {
130  PyObject *bytes;
131 
132  if (!(bytes = PyUnicode_AsEncodedString(obj, ENC_OPT, NULL)))
133  return NULL;
134 
135  if(PyBytes_AsStringAndSize(bytes, (char **) &str, NULL) == -1
136  || str == NULL)
137  {
138  Py_DECREF(bytes);
139  return NULL;
140  }
141 
142  *todecref = bytes;
143  }
144  else
145  {
146 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
147  PyErr_FORMAT(PyExc_TypeError,
148  N_("expected str() or unicode() instance, but got %s"),
149  Py_TYPE_NAME(obj));
150 #else
151  PyErr_FORMAT(PyExc_TypeError,
152  N_("expected bytes() or str() instance, but got %s"),
153  Py_TYPE_NAME(obj));
154 #endif
155  return NULL;
156  }
157 
158  return (char_u *) str;
159 }

166  static int
167 NumberToLong(PyObject *obj, long *result, int flags)
168 {
169 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
170  if (PyInt_Check(obj))
171  {
172  *result = PyInt_AsLong(obj);
173  if (PyErr_Occurred())
174  return -1;
175  }
176  else
177 #endif
178  if (PyLong_Check(obj))
179  {
180  *result = PyLong_AsLong(obj);
181  if (PyErr_Occurred())
182  return -1;
183  }
184  else if (PyNumber_Check(obj))
185  {
186  PyObject *num;
187 
188  if (!(num = PyNumber_Long(obj)))
189  return -1;
190 
191  *result = PyLong_AsLong(num);
192 
193  Py_DECREF(num);
194 
195  if (PyErr_Occurred())
196  return -1;
197  }
198  else
199  {
200 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
201  PyErr_FORMAT(PyExc_TypeError,
202  N_("expected int(), long() or something supporting "
203  "coercing to long(), but got %s"),
204  Py_TYPE_NAME(obj));
205 #else
206  PyErr_FORMAT(PyExc_TypeError,
207  N_("expected int() or something supporting coercing to int(), "
208  "but got %s"),
209  Py_TYPE_NAME(obj));
210 #endif
211  return -1;
212  }
213 
214  if (flags & NUMBER_INT)
215  {
216  if (*result > INT_MAX)
217  {
218  PyErr_SET_STRING(PyExc_OverflowError,
219  N_("value is too large to fit into C int type"));
220  return -1;
221  }
222  else if (*result < INT_MIN)
223  {
224  PyErr_SET_STRING(PyExc_OverflowError,
225  N_("value is too small to fit into C int type"));
226  return -1;
227  }
228  }
229 
230  if (flags & NUMBER_NATURAL)
231  {
232  if (*result <= 0)
233  {
234  PyErr_SET_STRING(PyExc_ValueError,
235  N_("number must be greater than zero"));
236  return -1;
237  }
238  }
239  else if (flags & NUMBER_UNSIGNED)
240  {
241  if (*result < 0)
242  {
243  PyErr_SET_STRING(PyExc_ValueError,
244  N_("number must be greater or equal to zero"));
245  return -1;
246  }
247  }
248 
249  return 0;
250 }

368  static void
369 writer(writefn fn, char_u *str, PyInt n)
370 {
371  char_u *ptr;
372 
373  /* Flush when switching output function. */
374  if (fn != old_fn)
375  PythonIO_Flush();
376  old_fn = fn;
377 
378  /* Write each NL separated line. Text after the last NL is kept for
379  * writing later. */
380  while (n > 0 && (ptr = memchr(str, '\n', n)) != NULL)
381  {
382  PyInt len = ptr - str;
383 
384  if (ga_grow(&io_ga, (int)(len + 1)) == FAIL)
385  break;
386 
387  mch_memmove(((char *)io_ga.ga_data) + io_ga.ga_len, str, (size_t)len);
388  ((char *)io_ga.ga_data)[io_ga.ga_len + len] = NUL;
389  fn((char_u *)io_ga.ga_data);
390  str = ptr + 1;
391  n -= len + 1;
392  io_ga.ga_len = 0;
393  }
394 
395  /* Put the remaining text into io_ga for later printing. */
396  if (n > 0 && ga_grow(&io_ga, (int)(n + 1)) == OK)
397  {
398  mch_memmove(((char *)io_ga.ga_data) + io_ga.ga_len, str, (size_t)n);
399  io_ga.ga_len += (int)n;
400  }
401 }

403  static int
404 write_output(OutputObject *self, PyObject *string)
405 {
406  Py_ssize_t len = 0;
407  char *str = NULL;
408  int error = self->error;
409 
410  if (!PyArg_Parse(string, "et#", ENC_OPT, &str, &len))
411  return -1;
412 
413  Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
414  Python_Lock_Vim();

435  static PyObject *
436 OutputWritelines(OutputObject *self, PyObject *seq)
437 {
438  PyObject *iterator;
439  PyObject *item;
440 
441  if (!(iterator = PyObject_GetIter(seq)))
442  return NULL;
443 
444  while ((item = PyIter_Next(iterator)))
445  {
446  if (write_output(self, item))
447  {
448  Py_DECREF(iterator);
449  Py_DECREF(item);
450  return NULL;
451  }
452  Py_DECREF(item);
453  }
454 
455  Py_DECREF(iterator);
456 
457  /* Iterator may have finished due to an exception */
458  if (PyErr_Occurred())
459  return NULL;
460 
461  Py_INCREF(Py_None);
462  return Py_None;
463 }

610  static int
611 VimTryEnd(void)
612 {
613  --trylevel;
614  /* Without this it stops processing all subsequent Vim script commands and
615  * generates strange error messages if I e.g. try calling Test() in a cycle
616  */
617  did_emsg = FALSE;
618  /* Keyboard interrupt should be preferred over anything else */
619  if (got_int)
620  {
621  if (did_throw)
622  discard_current_exception();
623  got_int = FALSE;
624  PyErr_SetNone(PyExc_KeyboardInterrupt);
625  return -1;
626  }
627  else if (msg_list != NULL && *msg_list != NULL)
628  {
629  int should_free;
630  char *msg;
631 
632  msg = get_exception_string(*msg_list, ET_ERROR, NULL, &should_free);
633 
634  if (msg == NULL)
635  {
636  PyErr_NoMemory();
637  return -1;
638  }
639 
640  PyErr_SetVim(msg);
641 
642  free_global_msglist();
643 
644  if (should_free)
645  vim_free(msg);
646 
647  return -1;
648  }
649  else if (!did_throw)
650  return (PyErr_Occurred() ? -1 : 0);
651  /* Python exception is preferred over vim one; unlikely to occur though */
652  else if (PyErr_Occurred())
653  {
654  discard_current_exception();
655  return -1;
656  }
657  /* Finally transform Vim script exception to python one */
658  else
659  {
660  PyErr_SetVim((char *)current_exception->value);
661  discard_current_exception();
662  return -1;
663  }
664 }

710 /*
711  * Function to translate a typval_T into a PyObject; this will recursively
712  * translate lists/dictionaries into their Python equivalents.
713  *
714  * The depth parameter is to avoid infinite recursion, set it to 1 when
715  * you call VimToPython.
716  */
717  static PyObject *
718 VimToPython(typval_T *our_tv, int depth, PyObject *lookup_dict)
719 {
720  PyObject *ret;
721  PyObject *newObj;
722  char ptrBuf[sizeof(void *) * 2 + 3];
723 
724  /* Avoid infinite recursion */
725  if (depth > 100)
726  {
727  Py_INCREF(Py_None);
728  ret = Py_None;
729  return ret;
730  }
731 
732  /* Check if we run into a recursive loop. The item must be in lookup_dict
733  * then and we can use it again. */
734  if ((our_tv->v_type == VAR_LIST && our_tv->vval.v_list != NULL)
735  || (our_tv->v_type == VAR_DICT && our_tv->vval.v_dict != NULL))
736  {
737  sprintf(ptrBuf, "%p",
738  our_tv->v_type == VAR_LIST ? (void *)our_tv->vval.v_list
739  : (void *)our_tv->vval.v_dict);
740 
741  if ((ret = PyDict_GetItemString(lookup_dict, ptrBuf)))
742  {
743  Py_INCREF(ret);
744  return ret;
745  }
746  }
747 
748  if (our_tv->v_type == VAR_STRING)
749  ret = PyString_FromString(our_tv->vval.v_string == NULL
750  ? "" : (char *)our_tv->vval.v_string);
751  else if (our_tv->v_type == VAR_NUMBER)
752  {
753  char buf[NUMBUFLEN];
754 
755  /* For backwards compatibility numbers are stored as strings. */
756  sprintf(buf, "%ld", (long)our_tv->vval.v_number);
757  ret = PyString_FromString((char *)buf);
758  }
759 #ifdef FEAT_FLOAT
760  else if (our_tv->v_type == VAR_FLOAT)
761  {
762  char buf[NUMBUFLEN];
763 
764  sprintf(buf, "%f", our_tv->vval.v_float);
765  ret = PyString_FromString((char *)buf);
766  }
767 #endif
768  else if (our_tv->v_type == VAR_LIST)
769  {
770  list_T *list = our_tv->vval.v_list;
771  listitem_T *curr;
772 
773  if (list == NULL)
774  return NULL;
775 
776  if (!(ret = PyList_New(0)))
777  return NULL;
778 
779  if (PyDict_SetItemString(lookup_dict, ptrBuf, ret))
780  {
781  Py_DECREF(ret);
782  return NULL;
783  }
784 
785  for (curr = list->lv_first; curr != NULL; curr = curr->li_next)
786  {
787  if (!(newObj = VimToPython(&curr->li_tv, depth + 1, lookup_dict)))
788  {
789  Py_DECREF(ret);
790  return NULL;
791  }
792  if (PyList_Append(ret, newObj))
793  {
794  Py_DECREF(newObj);
795  Py_DECREF(ret);
796  return NULL;
797  }
798  Py_DECREF(newObj);
799  }
800  }
801  else if (our_tv->v_type == VAR_DICT)
802  {
803 
804  hashtab_T *ht;
805  long_u todo;
806  hashitem_T *hi;
807  dictitem_T *di;
808 
809  if (our_tv->vval.v_dict == NULL)
810  return NULL;
811  ht = &our_tv->vval.v_dict->dv_hashtab;
812 
813  if (!(ret = PyDict_New()))
814  return NULL;
815 
816  if (PyDict_SetItemString(lookup_dict, ptrBuf, ret))
817  {
818  Py_DECREF(ret);
819  return NULL;
820  }
821 
822  todo = ht->ht_used;
823  for (hi = ht->ht_array; todo > 0; ++hi)
824  {
825  if (!HASHITEM_EMPTY(hi))
826  {
827  --todo;
828 
829  di = dict_lookup(hi);
830  if (!(newObj = VimToPython(&di->di_tv, depth + 1, lookup_dict)))
831  {
832  Py_DECREF(ret);
833  return NULL;
834  }
835  if (PyDict_SetItemString(ret, (char *)hi->hi_key, newObj))
836  {
837  Py_DECREF(ret);
838  Py_DECREF(newObj);
839  return NULL;
840  }
841  }
842  }
843  }
844  else if (our_tv->v_type == VAR_SPECIAL)
845  {
846  if (our_tv->vval.v_number == VVAL_FALSE)
847  {
848  ret = Py_False;
849  Py_INCREF(ret);
850  }
851  else if (our_tv->vval.v_number == VVAL_TRUE)
852  {
853  ret = Py_True;
854  Py_INCREF(ret);
855  }
856  else
857  {
858  Py_INCREF(Py_None);
859  ret = Py_None;
860  }
861  return ret;
862  }
863  else if (our_tv->v_type == VAR_BLOB)
864  ret = PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(
865  (char*) our_tv->vval.v_blob->bv_ga.ga_data,
866  (Py_ssize_t) our_tv->vval.v_blob->bv_ga.ga_len);
867  else
868  {
869  Py_INCREF(Py_None);
870  ret = Py_None;
871  }
872 
873  return ret;
874 }

876  static PyObject *
877 VimEval(PyObject *self UNUSED, PyObject *args)
878 {
879  char_u *expr;
880  typval_T *our_tv;
881  PyObject *string;
882  PyObject *todecref;
883  PyObject *ret;
884  PyObject *lookup_dict;
885 
886  if (!PyArg_ParseTuple(args, "O", &string))
887  return NULL;
888 
889  if (!(expr = StringToChars(string, &todecref)))
890  return NULL;
891 
892  Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
893  Python_Lock_Vim();
894  VimTryStart();
895  our_tv = eval_expr(expr, NULL);
896  Python_Release_Vim();
897  Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
898 
899  Py_XDECREF(todecref);
900 
901  if (VimTryEnd())
902  return NULL;
903 
904  if (our_tv == NULL)
905  {
906  PyErr_SET_VIM(N_("invalid expression"));
907  return NULL;
908  }
909 
910  /* Convert the Vim type into a Python type. Create a dictionary that's
911  * used to check for recursive loops. */
912  if (!(lookup_dict = PyDict_New()))
913  ret = NULL;
914  else
915  {
916  ret = VimToPython(our_tv, 1, lookup_dict);
917  Py_DECREF(lookup_dict);
918  }
919 
920 
921  Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS
922  Python_Lock_Vim();
923  free_tv(our_tv);
924  Python_Release_Vim();
925  Py_END_ALLOW_THREADS
926 
927  return ret;
928 }

1268  static PyObject *
1269 find_module(char *fullname, char *tail, PyObject *new_path)
1270 {
1271  PyObject *find_module_result;
1272  PyObject *module;
1273  char *dot;
1274 
1275  if ((dot = (char *)vim_strchr((char_u *) tail, '.')))
1276  {
1277  /*
1278  * There is a dot in the name: call find_module recursively without the
1279  * first component
1280  */
1281  PyObject *newest_path;
1282  int partlen = (int) (dot - 1 - tail);
1283 
1284  if (!(find_module_result = PyObject_CallFunction(py_find_module,
1285  "s#O", tail, partlen, new_path)))
1286  {
1287  if (PyErr_Occurred() && PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_ImportError))
1288  PyErr_Clear();
1289  return NULL;
1290  }
1291 
1292  if (!(module = call_load_module(
1293  fullname,
1294  ((int) (tail - fullname)) + partlen,
1295  find_module_result)))
1296  {
1297  Py_DECREF(find_module_result);
1298  return NULL;
1299  }
1300 
1301  Py_DECREF(find_module_result);
1302 
1303  if (!(newest_path = PyObject_GetAttrString(module, "__path__")))
1304  {
1305  Py_DECREF(module);
1306  return NULL;
1307  }
1308 
1309  Py_DECREF(module);
1310 
1311  find_module_result = find_module(fullname, dot + 1, newest_path);
1312 
1313  Py_DECREF(newest_path);
1314 
1315  return find_module_result;
1316  }
1317  else
1318  {
1319  if (!(find_module_result = PyObject_CallFunction(py_find_module,
1320  "sO", tail, new_path)))
1321  {
1322  if (PyErr_Occurred() && PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_ImportError))
1323  PyErr_Clear();
1324  return NULL;
1325  }
1326 
1327  return find_module_result;
1328  }
1329 }

3849  static PyObject *
3850 WindowNew(win_T *win, tabpage_T *tab)
3851 {
3852  /* We need to handle deletion of windows underneath us.
3853  * If we add a "w_python*_ref" field to the win_T structure,
3854  * then we can get at it in win_free() in vim. We then
3855  * need to create only ONE Python object per window - if
3856  * we try to create a second, just INCREF the existing one
3857  * and return it. The (single) Python object referring to
3858  * the window is stored in "w_python*_ref".
3859  * On a win_free() we set the Python object's win_T* field
3860  * to an invalid value. We trap all uses of a window
3861  * object, and reject them if the win_T* field is invalid.
3862  *
3863  * Python2 and Python3 get different fields and different objects:
3864  * w_python_ref and w_python3_ref fields respectively.
3865  */
3866 
3867  WindowObject *self;
3868 
3869  if (WIN_PYTHON_REF(win))
3870  {
3871  self = WIN_PYTHON_REF(win);
3872  Py_INCREF(self);
3873  }
3874  else
3875  {
3876  self = PyObject_GC_New(WindowObject, &WindowType);
3877  if (self == NULL)
3878  return NULL;
3879  self->win = win;
3880  WIN_PYTHON_REF(win) = self;
3881  }
3882 
3883  self->tabObject = ((TabPageObject *)(TabPageNew(tab)));
3884 
3885  return (PyObject *)(self);
3886 }

3895  PyObject_GC_Del((void *)(self));
3896 }

4192 /* Convert a Python string into a Vim line.
4193  *
4194  * The result is in allocated memory. All internal nulls are replaced by
4195  * newline characters. It is an error for the string to contain newline
4196  * characters.
4197  *
4198  * On errors, the Python exception data is set, and NULL is returned.
4199  */
4200  static char *
4201 StringToLine(PyObject *obj)
4202 {
4203  char *str;
4204  char *save;
4205  PyObject *bytes = NULL;
4206  Py_ssize_t len = 0;
4207  PyInt i;
4208  char *p;
4209 
4210  if (PyBytes_Check(obj))
4211  {
4212  if (PyBytes_AsStringAndSize(obj, &str, &len) == -1
4213  || str == NULL)
4214  return NULL;
4215  }
4216  else if (PyUnicode_Check(obj))
4217  {
4218  if (!(bytes = PyUnicode_AsEncodedString(obj, ENC_OPT, NULL)))
4219  return NULL;
4220 
4221  if (PyBytes_AsStringAndSize(bytes, &str, &len) == -1
4222  || str == NULL)
4223  {
4224  Py_DECREF(bytes);
4225  return NULL;
4226  }
4227  }
4228  else
4229  {
4230 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
4231  PyErr_FORMAT(PyExc_TypeError,
4232  N_("expected str() or unicode() instance, but got %s"),
4233  Py_TYPE_NAME(obj));
4234 #else
4235  PyErr_FORMAT(PyExc_TypeError,
4236  N_("expected bytes() or str() instance, but got %s"),
4237  Py_TYPE_NAME(obj));
4238 #endif
4239  return NULL;
4240  }
4241 
4242  /*
4243  * Error checking: String must not contain newlines, as we
4244  * are replacing a single line, and we must replace it with
4245  * a single line.
4246  * A trailing newline is removed, so that append(f.readlines()) works.
4247  */
4248  p = memchr(str, '\n', len);
4249  if (p != NULL)
4250  {
4251  if (p == str + len - 1)
4252  --len;
4253  else
4254  {
4255  PyErr_SET_VIM(N_("string cannot contain newlines"));
4256  Py_XDECREF(bytes);
4257  return NULL;
4258  }
4259  }
4260 
4261  /* Create a copy of the string, with internal nulls replaced by
4262  * newline characters, as is the vim convention.
4263  */
4264  save = alloc(len+1);
4265  if (save == NULL)
4266  {
4267  PyErr_NoMemory();
4268  Py_XDECREF(bytes);
4269  return NULL;
4270  }
4271 
4272  for (i = 0; i < len; ++i)
4273  {
4274  if (str[i] == '\0')
4275  save[i] = '\n';
4276  else
4277  save[i] = str[i];
4278  }
4279 
4280  save[i] = '\0';
4281  Py_XDECREF(bytes); /* Python 2 does nothing here */
4282 
4283  return save;
4284 }

4396  else

4502  RAISE_UNDO_FAIL;

4506  {
4507  if (ml_delete((linenr_T)lo, FALSE) == FAIL)
4508  {
4509  RAISE_DELETE_LINE_FAIL;
4510  break;
4511  }
4512  }

4515  /* Using an existing window for the buffer, adjust the cursor
4516  * position. */

4518  if (save_curbuf.br_buf == NULL)
4519  /* Only adjust marks if we managed to switch to a window that
4520  * holds the buffer, otherwise line numbers will be invalid. */
4521  deleted_lines_mark((linenr_T)lo, (long)i);
4522  }
4523

4527  return FAIL;
4528

4530  *len_change = -n;
4531 
4532  return OK;
4533  }
4534  else if (PyList_Check(list))
4535  {
4536  PyInt i;
4537  PyInt new_len = PyList_Size(list);
4538  PyInt old_len = hi - lo;
4539  PyInt extra = 0; /* lines added to text, can be negative */
4540  char **array;
4541 
4542  if (new_len == 0) /* avoid allocating zero bytes */
4543  array = NULL;
4544  else
4545  {
4546  array = PyMem_New(char *, new_len);
4547  if (array == NULL)
4548  {
4549  PyErr_NoMemory();

4551  }
4552  }

4555  {

4557

4559  !(array[i] = StringToLine(line)))
4560  {
4561  while (i)
4562  vim_free(array[--i]);
4563  PyMem_Free(array);
4564  return FAIL;
4565  }
4566  }

4570

4572  switch_to_win_for_buf(buf, &save_curwin, &save_curtab, &save_curbuf);
4573 
4574  if (u_save((linenr_T)(lo-1), (linenr_T)hi) == FAIL)
4575  RAISE_UNDO_FAIL;
4576

4578  * need to delete some old_len. We do this at the start, by
4579  * repeatedly deleting line "lo".
4580  */
4581  if (!PyErr_Occurred())
4582  {
4583  for (i = 0; i < old_len - new_len; ++i)
4584  if (ml_delete((linenr_T)lo, FALSE) == FAIL)
4585  {
4586  RAISE_DELETE_LINE_FAIL;
4587  break;
4588  }
4589  extra -= i;
4590  }
4591

4593  * new old_len. This is a more efficient operation, as it requires
4594  * less memory allocation and freeing.
4595  */
4596  if (!PyErr_Occurred())
4597  {
4598  for (i = 0; i < old_len && i < new_len; ++i)
4599  if (ml_replace((linenr_T)(lo+i), (char_u *)array[i], FALSE)
4600  == FAIL)
4601  {
4602  RAISE_REPLACE_LINE_FAIL;
4603  break;
4604  }
4605  }
4606  else
4607  i = 0;
4608 
4609  /* Now we may need to insert the remaining new old_len. If we do, we
4610  * must free the strings as we finish with them (we can't pass the
4611  * responsibility to vim in this case).
4612  */
4613  if (!PyErr_Occurred())
4614  {
4615  while (i < new_len)
4616  {
4617  if (ml_append((linenr_T)(lo + i - 1),
4618  (char_u *)array[i], 0, FALSE) == FAIL)
4619  {
4620  RAISE_INSERT_LINE_FAIL;
4621  break;
4622  }
4623  vim_free(array[i]);
4624  ++i;
4625  ++extra;
4626  }
4627  }
4628 
4629  /* Free any left-over old_len, as a result of an error */
4630  while (i < new_len)
4631  {
4632  vim_free(array[i]);
4633  ++i;
4634  }
4635 
4636  /* Free the array of old_len. All of its contents have now
4637  * been dealt with (either freed, or the responsibility passed
4638  * to vim.
4639  */
4640  PyMem_Free(array);

4643  * changed range, and move any in the remainder of the buffer.
4644  * Only adjust marks if we managed to switch to a window that holds
4645  * the buffer, otherwise line numbers will be invalid. */
4646  if (save_curbuf.br_buf == NULL)
4647  mark_adjust((linenr_T)lo, (linenr_T)(hi - 1),
4648  (long)MAXLNUM, (long)extra);
4649  changed_lines((linenr_T)lo, 0, (linenr_T)hi, (long)extra);

4652  || save_curbuf.br_buf == NULL))
4653  // Using an existing window for the buffer, adjust the cursor
4654  // position.
4655  py_fix_cursor((linenr_T)lo, (linenr_T)hi, (linenr_T)extra);
4656 
4657  /* END of region without "return". */
4658  restore_win_for_buf(save_curwin, save_curtab, &save_curbuf);
4659 
4660  if (VimTryEnd())
4661  return FAIL;
4662 
4663  if (len_change)
4664  *len_change = new_len - old_len;
4665 
4666  return OK;
4667  }
4668  else
4669  {
4670  PyErr_BadArgument();
4671  return FAIL;
4672  }

4675 /* Insert a number of lines into the specified buffer after the specified line.
4676  * The line number is in Vim format (1-based). The lines to be inserted are

4678  * to be added are checked for validity and correct format. Errors are
4679  * returned as a value of FAIL. The return value is OK on success.
4680  * If OK is returned and len_change is not NULL, *len_change

4694  {

4696

4705  RAISE_UNDO_FAIL;

4707  RAISE_INSERT_LINE_FAIL;

4710  * holds the buffer, otherwise line numbers will be invalid. */

4716

4718  return FAIL;
4719 
4720  if (len_change)
4721  *len_change = 1;
4722 
4723  return OK;
4724  }
4725  else if (PyList_Check(lines))
4726  {

4729  char **array;
4730

4733  {
4734  PyErr_NoMemory();

4744  {
4745  while (i)

4747  PyMem_Free(array);
4748  return FAIL;
4749  }
4750  }

4755

4757  RAISE_UNDO_FAIL;

4763  (char_u *)array[i], 0, FALSE) == FAIL)
4764  {

4766

4768  while (i < size)

4772  }

4782  * been freed. */

5125 {

5127  * If we add a "b_python*_ref" field to the buf_T structure,
5128  * then we can get at it in buf_freeall() in vim. We then
5129  * need to create only ONE Python object per buffer - if
5130  * we try to create a second, just INCREF the existing one
5131  * and return it. The (single) Python object referring to
5132  * the buffer is stored in "b_python*_ref".
5133  * Question: what to do on a buf_freeall(). We'll probably
5134  * have to either delete the Python object (DECREF it to
5135  * zero - a bad idea, as it leaves dangling refs!) or
5136  * set the buf_T * value to an invalid value (-1?), which
5137  * means we need checks in all access functions... Bah.
5138  *
5139  * Python2 and Python3 get different fields and different objects:
5140  * b_python_ref and b_python3_ref fields respectively.
5141  */
5142 
5143  BufferObject *self;
5144 
5145  if (BUF_PYTHON_REF(buf) != NULL)
5146  {
5147  self = BUF_PYTHON_REF(buf);
5148  Py_INCREF(self);
5149  }
5150  else
5151  {

5153  if (self == NULL)
5154  return NULL;
5155  self->buf = buf;
5156  BUF_PYTHON_REF(buf) = self;
5157  }
5158 
5159  return (PyObject *)(self);
5160 }

5673 static const char *code_hdr = "def " DOPY_FUNC "(line, linenr):\n ";
5674 static int code_hdr_len = 30;
5675 
5676  static void
5677 run_do(const char *cmd, void *arg UNUSED
5678 #ifdef PY_CAN_RECURSE
5679  , PyGILState_STATE *pygilstate
5680 #endif
5681  )
5682 {
5683  PyInt lnum;
5684  size_t len;
5685  char *code;
5686  int status;
5687  PyObject *pyfunc, *pymain;
5688  PyObject *run_ret;
5689  buf_T *was_curbuf = curbuf;
5690 
5691  if (u_save((linenr_T)RangeStart - 1, (linenr_T)RangeEnd + 1) != OK)
5692  {
5693  emsg(_("cannot save undo information"));
5694  return;
5695  }
5696 
5697  len = code_hdr_len + STRLEN(cmd);
5698  code = PyMem_New(char, len + 1);
5699  memcpy(code, code_hdr, code_hdr_len);
5700  STRCPY(code + code_hdr_len, cmd);
5701  run_ret = PyRun_String(code, Py_file_input, globals, globals);
5702  status = -1;
5703  if (run_ret != NULL)
5704  {
5705  status = 0;
5706  Py_DECREF(run_ret);
5707  }
5708  else if (PyErr_Occurred() && PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_SystemExit))
5709  {
5710  PyMem_Free(code);
5711  semsg(_(e_py_systemexit), "python");
5712  PyErr_Clear();
5713  return;
5714  }
5715  else
5716  PyErr_PrintEx(1);
5717 
5718  PyMem_Free(code);
5719 
5720  if (status)
5721  {
5722  emsg(_("failed to run the code"));
5723  return;
5724  }
5725 
5726  status = 0;
5727  pymain = PyImport_AddModule("__main__");
5728  pyfunc = PyObject_GetAttrString(pymain, DOPY_FUNC);
5729 #ifdef PY_CAN_RECURSE
5730  PyGILState_Release(*pygilstate);
5731 #endif
5732 
5733  for (lnum = RangeStart; lnum <= RangeEnd; ++lnum)
5734  {
5735  PyObject *line;
5736  PyObject *linenr;
5737  PyObject *ret;
5738 
5739 #ifdef PY_CAN_RECURSE
5740  *pygilstate = PyGILState_Ensure();
5741 #endif
5742  /* Check the line number, the command my have deleted lines. */
5743  if (lnum > curbuf->b_ml.ml_line_count
5744  || !(line = GetBufferLine(curbuf, lnum)))
5745  goto err;
5746  if (!(linenr = PyInt_FromLong((long) lnum)))
5747  {
5748  Py_DECREF(line);
5749  goto err;
5750  }
5751  ret = PyObject_CallFunctionObjArgs(pyfunc, line, linenr, NULL);
5752  Py_DECREF(line);
5753  Py_DECREF(linenr);
5754  if (!ret)
5755  goto err;
5756 
5757  /* Check that the command didn't switch to another buffer. */
5758  if (curbuf != was_curbuf)
5759  {
5760  Py_XDECREF(ret);
5761  goto err;
5762  }
5763 
5764  if (ret != Py_None)
5765  if (SetBufferLine(curbuf, lnum, ret, NULL) == FAIL)
5766  {
5767  Py_XDECREF(ret);
5768  goto err;
5769  }
5770 
5771  Py_XDECREF(ret);
5772  PythonIO_Flush();
5773 #ifdef PY_CAN_RECURSE
5774  PyGILState_Release(*pygilstate);
5775 #endif
5776  }
5777  goto out;
5778 err:
5779 #ifdef PY_CAN_RECURSE
5780  *pygilstate = PyGILState_Ensure();
5781 #endif
5782  PyErr_PrintEx(0);
5783  PythonIO_Flush();
5784  status = 1;
5785 out:
5786 #ifdef PY_CAN_RECURSE
5787  if (!status)
5788  *pygilstate = PyGILState_Ensure();
5789 #endif
5790  Py_DECREF(pyfunc);
5791  PyObject_SetAttrString(pymain, DOPY_FUNC, NULL);
5792  if (status)
5793  return;
5794  check_cursor();
5795  update_curbuf(NOT_VALID);
5796 }

5945  clear_tv(&di->di_tv);
5946  vim_free(di);
5947  dict_unref(dict);
5948  return -1;
5949  }
5950  }
5951 
5952  --dict->dv_refcount;
5953  return 0;
5954 }

5956  static int
5957 pymap_to_tv(PyObject *obj, typval_T *tv, PyObject *lookup_dict)
5958 {
5959  dict_T *dict;
5960  char_u *key;
5961  dictitem_T *di;
5962  PyObject *list;
5963  PyObject *iterator;
5964  PyObject *keyObject;
5965  PyObject *valObject;
5966 
5967  if (!(dict = py_dict_alloc()))
5968  return -1;
5969 
5970  tv->v_type = VAR_DICT;
5971  tv->vval.v_dict = dict;
5972 
5973  if (!(list = PyMapping_Keys(obj)))
5974  {
5975  dict_unref(dict);
5976  return -1;
5977  }
5978 
5979  if (!(iterator = PyObject_GetIter(list)))
5980  {
5981  dict_unref(dict);
5982  Py_DECREF(list);
5983  return -1;
5984  }
5985  Py_DECREF(list);
5986 
5987  while ((keyObject = PyIter_Next(iterator)))
5988  {
5989  PyObject *todecref;
5990 
5991  if (!(key = StringToChars(keyObject, &todecref)))
5992  {
5993  Py_DECREF(keyObject);
5994  Py_DECREF(iterator);
5995  dict_unref(dict);
5996  return -1;
5997  }
5998 
5999  if (*key == NUL)
6000  {
6001  Py_DECREF(keyObject);
6002  Py_DECREF(iterator);
6003  Py_XDECREF(todecref);
6004  dict_unref(dict);
6005  RAISE_NO_EMPTY_KEYS;
6006  return -1;
6007  }
6008 
6009  if (!(valObject = PyObject_GetItem(obj, keyObject)))
6010  {
6011  Py_DECREF(keyObject);
6012  Py_DECREF(iterator);
6013  Py_XDECREF(todecref);
6014  dict_unref(dict);
6015  return -1;
6016  }
6017 
6018  di = dictitem_alloc(key);
6019 
6020  Py_DECREF(keyObject);
6021  Py_XDECREF(todecref);
6022 
6023  if (di == NULL)
6024  {
6025  Py_DECREF(iterator);
6026  Py_DECREF(valObject);
6027  dict_unref(dict);
6028  PyErr_NoMemory();
6029  return -1;
6030  }
6031 
6032  if (_ConvertFromPyObject(valObject, &di->di_tv, lookup_dict) == -1)
6033  {
6034  Py_DECREF(iterator);
6035  Py_DECREF(valObject);
6036  vim_free(di);
6037  dict_unref(dict);
6038  return -1;
6039  }
6040 
6041  Py_DECREF(valObject);
6042 
6043  if (dict_add(dict, di) == FAIL)
6044  {
6045  RAISE_KEY_ADD_FAIL(di->di_key);
6046  Py_DECREF(iterator);
6047  dictitem_free(di);
6048  dict_unref(dict);
6049  return -1;
6050  }
6051  }
6052  Py_DECREF(iterator);
6053  --dict->dv_refcount;
6054  return 0;
6055 }

6078 typedef int (*pytotvfunc)(PyObject *, typval_T *, PyObject *);
6079 
6080  static int
6081 convert_dl(PyObject *obj, typval_T *tv,
6082  pytotvfunc py_to_tv, PyObject *lookup_dict)
6083 {
6084  PyObject *capsule;
6085  char hexBuf[sizeof(void *) * 2 + 3];
6086 
6087  sprintf(hexBuf, "%p", (void *)obj);
6088 
6089 #ifdef PY_USE_CAPSULE
6090  capsule = PyDict_GetItemString(lookup_dict, hexBuf);
6091 #else
6092  capsule = (PyObject *)PyDict_GetItemString(lookup_dict, hexBuf);
6093 #endif
6094  if (capsule == NULL)
6095  {
6096 #ifdef PY_USE_CAPSULE
6097  capsule = PyCapsule_New(tv, NULL, NULL);
6098 #else
6099  capsule = PyCObject_FromVoidPtr(tv, NULL);
6100 #endif
6101  if (PyDict_SetItemString(lookup_dict, hexBuf, capsule))
6102  {
6103  Py_DECREF(capsule);
6104  tv->v_type = VAR_UNKNOWN;
6105  return -1;
6106  }
6107 
6108  Py_DECREF(capsule);
6109 
6110  if (py_to_tv(obj, tv, lookup_dict) == -1)
6111  {
6112  tv->v_type = VAR_UNKNOWN;
6113  return -1;
6114  }
6115  /* As we are not using copy_tv which increments reference count we must
6116  * do it ourself. */
6117  if (tv->v_type == VAR_DICT)
6118  ++tv->vval.v_dict->dv_refcount;
6119  else if (tv->v_type == VAR_LIST)
6120  ++tv->vval.v_list->lv_refcount;
6121  }
6122  else
6123  {
6124  typval_T *v;
6125 
6126 #ifdef PY_USE_CAPSULE
6127  v = PyCapsule_GetPointer(capsule, NULL);
6128 #else
6129  v = PyCObject_AsVoidPtr(capsule);
6130 #endif
6131  copy_tv(v, tv);
6132  }
6133  return 0;
6134 }

6136  static int
6137 ConvertFromPyMapping(PyObject *obj, typval_T *tv)
6138 {

6140  int ret;
6141 
6142  if (!(lookup_dict = PyDict_New()))
6143  return -1;
6144

6146  {
6147  tv->v_type = VAR_DICT;
6148  tv->vval.v_dict = (((DictionaryObject *)(obj))->dict);
6149  ++tv->vval.v_dict->dv_refcount;

6209  static int
6210 _ConvertFromPyObject(PyObject *obj, typval_T *tv, PyObject *lookup_dict)
6211 {
6212  if (PyType_IsSubtype(obj->ob_type, &DictionaryType))
6213  {
6214  tv->v_type = VAR_DICT;
6215  tv->vval.v_dict = (((DictionaryObject *)(obj))->dict);
6216  ++tv->vval.v_dict->dv_refcount;
6217  }
6218  else if (PyType_IsSubtype(obj->ob_type, &ListType))
6219  {
6220  tv->v_type = VAR_LIST;
6221  tv->vval.v_list = (((ListObject *)(obj))->list);
6222  ++tv->vval.v_list->lv_refcount;
6223  }
6224  else if (PyType_IsSubtype(obj->ob_type, &FunctionType))
6225  {
6226  FunctionObject *func = (FunctionObject *) obj;
6227  if (func->self != NULL || func->argv != NULL)
6228  {
6229  partial_T *pt = ALLOC_CLEAR_ONE(partial_T);
6230 
6231  set_partial(func, pt, TRUE);
6232  tv->vval.v_partial = pt;
6233  tv->v_type = VAR_PARTIAL;
6234  }
6235  else
6236  {
6237  if (set_string_copy(func->name, tv) == -1)
6238  return -1;
6239 
6240  tv->v_type = VAR_FUNC;
6241  }
6242  func_ref(func->name);
6243  }
6244  else if (PyBytes_Check(obj))
6245  {
6246  char_u *str;
6247 
6248  if (PyBytes_AsStringAndSize(obj, (char **) &str, NULL) == -1)
6249  return -1;
6250  if (str == NULL)
6251  return -1;
6252 
6253  if (set_string_copy(str, tv) == -1)
6254  return -1;
6255 
6256  tv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
6257  }
6258  else if (PyUnicode_Check(obj))
6259  {
6260  PyObject *bytes;
6261  char_u *str;
6262 
6263  bytes = PyUnicode_AsEncodedString(obj, ENC_OPT, NULL);
6264  if (bytes == NULL)
6265  return -1;
6266 
6267  if(PyBytes_AsStringAndSize(bytes, (char **) &str, NULL) == -1)
6268  return -1;
6269  if (str == NULL)
6270  return -1;
6271 
6272  if (set_string_copy(str, tv))
6273  {
6274  Py_XDECREF(bytes);
6275  return -1;
6276  }
6277  Py_XDECREF(bytes);
6278 
6279  tv->v_type = VAR_STRING;
6280  }
6281 #if PY_MAJOR_VERSION < 3
6282  else if (PyInt_Check(obj))
6283  {
6284  tv->v_type = VAR_NUMBER;
6285  tv->vval.v_number = (varnumber_T) PyInt_AsLong(obj);
6286  if (PyErr_Occurred())
6287  return -1;
6288  }
6289 #endif
6290  else if (PyLong_Check(obj))
6291  {
6292  tv->v_type = VAR_NUMBER;
6293  tv->vval.v_number = (varnumber_T) PyLong_AsLong(obj);
6294  if (PyErr_Occurred())
6295  return -1;
6296  }
6297  else if (PyDict_Check(obj))
6298  return convert_dl(obj, tv, pydict_to_tv, lookup_dict);
6299 #ifdef FEAT_FLOAT
6300  else if (PyFloat_Check(obj))
6301  {
6302  tv->v_type = VAR_FLOAT;
6303  tv->vval.v_float = (float_T) PyFloat_AsDouble(obj);
6304  }
6305 #endif
6306  else if (PyObject_HasAttrString(obj, "keys"))
6307  return convert_dl(obj, tv, pymap_to_tv, lookup_dict);
6308  /* PyObject_GetIter can create built-in iterator for any sequence object */
6309  else if (PyIter_Check(obj) || PySequence_Check(obj))
6310  return convert_dl(obj, tv, pyseq_to_tv, lookup_dict);
6311  else if (PyMapping_Check(obj))
6312  return convert_dl(obj, tv, pymap_to_tv, lookup_dict);
6313  else if (PyNumber_Check(obj))
6314  {
6315  PyObject *num;
6316 
6317  if (!(num = PyNumber_Long(obj)))
6318  return -1;
6319 
6320  tv->v_type = VAR_NUMBER;
6321  tv->vval.v_number = (varnumber_T) PyLong_AsLong(num);
6322 
6323  Py_DECREF(num);
6324  }
6325  else if (obj == Py_None)
6326  {
6327  tv->v_type = VAR_SPECIAL;
6328  tv->vval.v_number = VVAL_NONE;
6329  }
6330  else
6331  {
6332  PyErr_FORMAT(PyExc_TypeError,
6333  N_("unable to convert %s to vim structure"),
6334  Py_TYPE_NAME(obj));
6335  return -1;
6336  }
6337  return 0;
6338 }
6339 
6340  static PyObject *
6341 ConvertToPyObject(typval_T *tv)
6342 {
6343  typval_T *argv;
6344  int i;
6345  if (tv == NULL)
6346  {
6347  PyErr_SET_VIM(N_("internal error: NULL reference passed"));
6348  return NULL;
6349  }
6350  switch (tv->v_type)
6351  {
6352  case VAR_STRING:
6353  return PyBytes_FromString(tv->vval.v_string == NULL
6354  ? "" : (char *)tv->vval.v_string);
6355  case VAR_NUMBER:
6356  return PyLong_FromLong((long) tv->vval.v_number);
6357 #ifdef FEAT_FLOAT
6358  case VAR_FLOAT:
6359  return PyFloat_FromDouble((double) tv->vval.v_float);
6360 #endif
6361  case VAR_LIST:
6362  return NEW_LIST(tv->vval.v_list);
6363  case VAR_DICT:
6364  return NEW_DICTIONARY(tv->vval.v_dict);
6365  case VAR_FUNC:
6366  return NEW_FUNCTION(tv->vval.v_string == NULL
6367  ? (char_u *)"" : tv->vval.v_string,
6368  0, NULL, NULL, TRUE);
6369  case VAR_PARTIAL:
6370  if (tv->vval.v_partial->pt_argc)
6371  {
6372  argv = PyMem_New(typval_T, (size_t)tv->vval.v_partial->pt_argc);
6373  for (i = 0; i < tv->vval.v_partial->pt_argc; i++)
6374  copy_tv(&tv->vval.v_partial->pt_argv[i], &argv[i]);
6375  }
6376  else
6377  argv = NULL;
6378  if (tv->vval.v_partial->pt_dict != NULL)
6379  tv->vval.v_partial->pt_dict->dv_refcount++;
6380  return NEW_FUNCTION(tv->vval.v_partial == NULL
6381  ? (char_u *)"" : partial_name(tv->vval.v_partial),
6382  tv->vval.v_partial->pt_argc, argv,
6383  tv->vval.v_partial->pt_dict,
6384  tv->vval.v_partial->pt_auto);
6385  case VAR_BLOB:
6386  return PyBytes_FromStringAndSize(
6387  (char*) tv->vval.v_blob->bv_ga.ga_data,
6388  (Py_ssize_t) tv->vval.v_blob->bv_ga.ga_len);
6389  case VAR_UNKNOWN:
6390  case VAR_CHANNEL:
6391  case VAR_JOB:
6392  Py_INCREF(Py_None);
6393  return Py_None;
6394  case VAR_SPECIAL:
6395  switch (tv->vval.v_number)
6396  {
6397  case VVAL_FALSE: return AlwaysFalse(NULL);
6398  case VVAL_TRUE: return AlwaysTrue(NULL);
6399  case VVAL_NONE:
6400  case VVAL_NULL: return AlwaysNone(NULL);
6401  }
6402  PyErr_SET_VIM(N_("internal error: invalid value type"));
6403  return NULL;
6404  }
6405  return NULL;
6406 }

6706  Py_DECREF(path_hook);

6718  VimTryEnd(); /* Discard the error */
